<br>
Our point system seems to be working very well and I don't think VE will be raiding anything with totally in house folks.  In fact it's raid policy that 1/4 of our raid consists of those who are not VE members and typically try to fill them with people we don't know.<br>
<br>
The trick was finding a point system that rewarded people for activity but didn't make it so overwhelming that it would ward other people from joining.<br>
<br>
We did a compromise.  First off we made sure that no one would ever be completely out on an item.  You always get at least 1 number on anything you CaWU.  Secondly to insure that people didn't rack up enormous amounts of points, we made the number of points received low (1 per raid) and made it policy that anytime points were used to win an item, they then were returned to 0.<br>
<br>
I wrote a quick simple CGI that updates the points automatically so record keeping is real easy too.  It gives small rewards for those who raid with us often, but doesn't lock down those who are new to raid with us.  It's a fairly delicate balance, but it does work well.<br>
<br>
That doesn't mean it would suit everyone, but just saying we're about as non-In House as you can get and we've made it work well and it does serve the purpose of what we wanted.  Which was rewarding those who help out without taking from those just coming in. <p><br>
